The paper proposes two algorithms for fair machine learning, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The algorithms also involve meta-learning and model-agnostic approaches, which could fall under the cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses computer vision datasets for experimentation, which could also place it under the computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
